Ben Foakes uses his feet well and flicks this one through mid-wicket, to wide long on for a single.
Full, flighted, on middle, Ben keeps it out.
Was that a catch? Short and turning back in. Leach looks to defend but the ball cuts him in half. It goes very close to the glove. Pant, behind the stumps, cannot hold onto it either.
Floated on middle and leg, Leach defends it to the on side.
Floated on off, Foakes flicks it towards mid-wicket and gets a run.
Short and on off and middle. Foakes manages to get his bat down in time as the ball kept low.
Whacked over to the leg side but there is Rohit Sharma guarding the boundary on the leg side. Just a run.
Flighted on middle and off, Leach defends it.
Darted on the pads, Foakes looks to defend but misses and gets hit on the pad away from the stump.
On the pads and short. Foakes flicks it behind square on the leg side. He looks for a run but does not get it.
On the pads, Foakes flicks it to mid-wicket.
Good take! Short and spinning away, Foakes looks to flick but misses as the ball tums a mile. Pant does well to take the ball behind the stump.
Tossed up on off, Foakes defends it.
Floated outside off, Foakes looks to whip it to the leg side but misses and gets hit on the pad outside the line of off stump.
Shorter on off, Leach defends it off the back foot to see off the over.
SIX! Where has that come from! Leach has put on his dancing shoes and got off the mark with a biggie! Floated on off, Leach comes down the track and whacks it with the spin over long on for a biggie.
Flighted on off, Leach defends it off the back foot.
Flighted around leg, Leach comes down the track and looks to whack it on the leg side. He misses and gets hit on the pad.
Darted on middle and leg, Leach looks to defend but misses. Going down leg hence the muted appeal is turned down.
Floated on off, Ben manages to squirt it behind point for a run.
Play and a miss! Floated around off, Leach looks to play but misses.
Floated on off, Leach manages to keep it out.
Tossed up on off, Leach blocks it.
Floated on middle, Leach defends it.

OUT! LBW! As plumb as it gets! Ashwin gets his 400th Test wicket and India or shall we say the Indian spinners have spun a web around the England batters, which they have not been able to get past. Darted fuller on middle, Archer looks to whack it across the line. He misses and gets hit on the pad. An appeal follows and the umpire raises the finger. Archer decides to send it upstairs. No saving the big man as Ultra Edge first shows no bat and then Ball Tracker shows all red. Victim number 400 for Ashwin and he becomes the second fastest to the feat. He is happy and so are his teammates. He shows the ball to the crowd and he might keep this pink ball.
Jack Leach walks out, with blade in hand now!
Review time! Ashwin has got his 400th wicket according to the umpire but Archer has decided to try his luck with the review.
Around off, full, kept out.
Flighted on off, Foakes drives it through covers and gets a couple.
Quicker ball on the pads, Foakes looks to flick but misses and gets hit on the pad.
Flighted on off, Foakes looks to defend but the ball grips away and beats the outside edge of Ben's willow. Pant too cannot hold onto it.
Tossed up on middle, Foakes pushes it back to the bowler.
On the stumps, Foakes keeps it out.
EDGED BUT FALLS SHORT! Short around off, Foakes looks to defend but the ball turns and hits the outside edge. Foakes does well to dab it away from the man at second slip.

OUT! BOWLED! Ashwin gets the better of Pope. AGAIN!  Another one bites the dust and England are into the bowlers now. Floated delivery pitching on middle, Pope looks to defend but the ball pitches, turns and bounces away from him. The Englishman is completely squared up as the ball goes past the outside edge to hit the off pole. 6 down for 66 but effectively the tourists are 33/6!
Into the bowlers now! Jofra Archer walks out.

FOUR! That has beaten everyone! Oh there is some glove! Ashwin bowls this slower and gives this air around off. Pope looks to sweep but misses it. Pant misses it as well and the ball goes to the fence. Ashwin is surprised that it has been given as a boundary.
Floated on off, Pope defends it.
Flighted on middle, Foakes pushes it to the left of mid on and takes a run.
Tossed up on off, Foakes defends it to mid on.
Floated on off, Foakes defends it to the leg side with the spin.
A very loopy ball around off. Pope pushes it to mid off. When he does that, there is a host of dust that puffs out of the surface.
Flighted on off, Pope blocks it.
Quick single! Floated on off, Foakes pushes it to the right of Washington Sundar at mid off and takes a quick run.
Darted on leg and skidding away. Foakes looks to defend but misses and gets hit on the pad.
Tossed up around off, Foakes gets on his front foot to defend but the ball turns and beats his outside edge.
Flighted from wide off the crease. Foakes lunges forward and blocks it.

EDGED BUT AWAY! Floated on middle and leg, Pope looks to defend but gets an inside edge courtesy an inside edge. The ball lobs off his pad and luckily for Ollie it falls away from Shubman Gill at short leg.
A nicely looped up delivery on middle. Foakes flicks it to the leg side and gets his first run of the game.
Flighted around off, Foakes defends it off the front foot.
Flighted around off, Pope turns it to square leg and gets to the other end.
Tossed up around leg, Pope comes out in desperation and looks to whack one over on the leg side. He misses and gets hit on the pad.
Shorter on off, Pope punches it to cover and gets a couple,
Floated outside off, Foakes leaves it alone.

OUT! LBW! The big wicket, the big fish, the England captain Joe Root, who was looking good out in the middle is out of here and England have half their side back in the hut with the lead just at 23. Axar gets his 10th of the game and playing just his second Test, he now has a 10-wicket game as well. What a bowler! No Jadeja, no problem. The local by has done the job for his nation here at his home venue. Tremendous feeling for Axar. He would have dreamt of this moment as a child and he has achieved his dreams. The round arm action of Axar once again does the trick. Floated on middle, the ball skids off the surface and comes straight. Root looks to defend but gets beaten and the ball hits him on the pad. A huge appeal follows and the umpire raises his finger. Root does not even bother reviewing this as he knew that this one was plumb.
Half the side back into the shed now and Ben Foakes comes out for the visitors!
Flatter on middle, Pope punches it to mid on and takes a quick run.
Another beauty! Pope is dancing against the turning ball so far! Floated around off, Pope looks to defend but misses and it goes past the outside edge.
Tossed up on off, Root sweeps it towards square leg and gets a single.
Floated on middle, Root defends it with a straight bat.
FOUR. Ollie Pope gets off the mark with a reverse sweep. This is on middle, full, flighted, Pope gets low and reverse sweeps this one to the third man fence.
Flighted on middle, Ollie comes down the track and pushes this to the on side.
Outside off, left alone by Pope.
Floated around off, Pope looks to push it away but fails to get any bat on this.
Ollie Pope will join his skipper out in the middle. Can he continue from Stokes left off? Not an easy pitch to bat on especially when you're new at the crease.

DRINKS! WOW! What a fascinating watch this has been. England have lost yet another wicket and they are reeling at 50/4 with a paltry lead of 17. Just when it looked like a partnership was building between Stokes and Root, the former has departed once again to Ashwin who clearly is winning the mental battle against Stokes. England need something to play with. No matter how good the pitch is to bowl on, they need something over 100 minimum to have some chance.  India will be happy with how things have panned out post their collapse. Just two bowlers used and they have done the job perfectly.

OUT! LBW! Ashwin gets his bunny again and this is the 11th time that Ashwin has got Stokes in Tests! The fourth wicket falls now and Stokes' poor run in this series will continue. Ashwin bowls a full ball, gives it nice loop and lands it around off and middle, Stokes comes ahead and looks to block this one out but misses. Gets rapped on the pad and the Indians go up, in appeal. The umpire does not take long to raise his finger. Stokes walks across to his skipper, Root and has a chat but Ben has a look, of someone who is not too confident. He looks to walk back, but Joe stops him and it looks like they will go for it, with around 2 seconds left on the timer. But, in the end, Ben probably says no and decides to walk off. India doing well to chip at these wickets. England leading by 17 runs.
Darted on leg, Ben looks to block but misses and get hit on the pad.
That is defended solidly off the front foot.
An inside edge this time. Floated and around off, Root prods ahead and looks to block this one out but inside edges it, onto his pad. An appeal but the umpire shakes his head.
Tossed up and on middle, Ben sweeps this one to fine leg. One run.
On off, played towards point.
Tossed up and around off, Stokes gets low and looks to sweep this one but misses and gets rapped on the pad. The impact was outside off and hence, there is not much of an appeal.
Short, wide, outside off, slapped away through point for one.
Reverse sweep now. Floated on middle and off, Joe reverse sweeps it behind point and keeps the strike.
Sharp spin and bounce. Root looks to defend it outside the line of off pole but misses and gets hit high on the pad.
Darted quicker on middle and leg, Root blocks it.
Floated on off, Root pushes it back to the bowler.
Flighted fuller outside off, Stokes pushes it to point for a single.
Good ball! Short and turning away with some extra bounce. Stokes looks to defend but misses and gets hit high on his back leg's thigh pad.
That is defended solidly off the front foot.
Outside off, loopy, spins away and Joe misses his push away.

NOT OUT! Root survives! A very close call but the benefit of the doubt goes to Root! Patel bowls a full, tossed up ball just around off, Root comes ahead and looks to block this one out. Is not able to do so and gets smothered on the pads. A very loud appeal by the Indians and this time, the umpire raises his finger. Joe Root comes ahead and decides to have a chat with his partner, Stokes and in the end, makes the 'T' symbol. The ball is in between the bat and the pad and so, the third umpire has a couple of looks at this one, from different angles too. It seems to be real close and in the end, the third umpire decides to go the way of the batter and has the on-field umpire reverse the decision.
A very hopeful review from Joe Root.  He has been adjudged LBW but after a long chat with Stokes he has decided to signal the 'T' in the very end.
The batsman has just blocked that from his crease.
Shorter and on the middle and leg pole, Root goes back and looks to push this one away to the leg side but misses and gets hit on the pad. An appeal but nothing from the umpire.
Around off, short, clipped through mid-wicket for a couple.
Beauty to end the over. Flighted on off, Stokes looks to defend but the ball turns and beats the outside edge of Stokes' willow.
Flighted around off, Stokes looks to push it on the off side. The ball hits the outside edge and goes wide of second slip. Two taken. Takes the lead to 11!
Tossed up on off, Stokes gets on his front foot and defends it onto the ground.
Flighted outside off, Stokes looks to play but misses. The ball hits Pant's glove and goes to Kohli at second slip.
FOUR! Reverse sweep now! Stokes has decided to take the attack now. Floated on middle and off, Stokes reverse sweeps it through point for a boundary.
FOUR! Incredible shot! Short and around leg, Stokes gets on his back foot and punches it off his back foot through mid-wicket. It has been hit with power and it goes to the fence.
Flighted outside off, Root looks to play at this one but the ball turns away and goes past the bat, to Rahane, at first slip.
On middle, swept away to square leg for one. England leading by one now!
Flighted around off, Joe pushes this one towards covers for one.
Joe Root has just blocked that from his crease.
Pushed to the off side now by Joe.
The batsman has just blocked that from his crease.

IN THE AIR...SAFE! Ben survives a scare. He was looking to take the charge but he does not lose the wicket on this occasion. Flighted, around off, Stokes goes for the sweep again but only manages to generate a top edge. Goes high up and lands in no man's land near mid-wicket. Two runs.
FOUR. Much needed boundary for England. They are now behind by 3 runs. Flighted, around off, Stokes gets low and sweeps this one through mid-wicket.
A full ball, loopy, Stokes presses forward and defends.
On off, pushed to covers.
Big turn. Flighted around off, turns away with venom as Ben misses his defensive push.
Full, almost yorker length, on middle, well dug out.
Worked behind square on the leg side for one run. England still behind by 7 runs.
Full, on middle, shoots up after hitting the deck and hits him high on the pad.
On middle again, kept out by Ben.
Darted on middle, shorter in length, clipped to the mid-wicket fielder.
Ben Stokes goes on the back foot and blocks.
Clipped to the on side for a single.

An appeal but turned down. Full, outside off, tossed up, Ben looks to sweep but misses and gets hit on the pad. Turned down by the umpire and there is some discussion, as to whether they need to take the review. Do not go for it in the end.
EDGY...SHORT! Tossed up and around off, Stokes looks to block but the ball takes the outside edge and goes and drops just in front of Virat, at second slip.
Arm ball around off, Stokes blocks.
SWEEP AND A MISS. Flighted and around off, turns away and takes off after hitting the deck, Ben gets on his knees and looks to sweep this one away. Misses though.
Short, on the pad, clipped through mid-wicket for a brace.
Full, floated, around off, pushed to the mid on region.
Full, loopy, around off, whipped through mid-wicket for one. Another successful over from Axar. 3 runs but also a wicket off this one.
Short, around middle, defended to the on side.
Stokes gets off the mark straightaway. Flatter, around middle, Stokes clips this one behind square on the leg side for a brace.
The deputy joins the skipper out in the middle. Ben Stokes walks out to bat now.

OUT! CAUGHT! The third wicket for Axar and England lose another one. Top decision from the on-field umpire! Axar gives this one air and lands it around off, Sibley gets on his knees and looks to slog sweep this one away to the leg side. Misses and the ball goes past him, into Pant's mitts. A loud appeal from the Indians and the umpire raises his finger. Hmm...Sibley takes the review straightaway, does not even consult Root, which would suggest that he knows he has not got any bat on this. Well, Sibley, looks like you were wrong as Ultra Edge shows a clear spike as the ball is going past the bat. The on-field decision stays and the local lad, Patel is on a roll. England are behind by 14 runs.
Sibley has been adjudged caught behind. He though is not convinced and has decided to take the review straightaway.
Tossed up and around off, Dom comes ahead and blocks.
Shortish, on off, nudged to square leg now.
A chance to take the catch! Flighted on middle, Root just tucks this one in front of the short leg fielder but the ball falls short. Joe has a wry smile on this face.
Flat, on off, Joe goes on the back foot and clips this one to short mid-wicket.
Around off, shorter in length, Joe pushes this one away to the off side.
Darted on middle again, spinning down leg as Root shoulders arms now.
On middle, tucked to the leg side.
Flighted, on middle, turns into Joe as he goes back and punches to the left of mid on for a couple of runs. England behind by 14 runs now.
On off, fuller, loopy, Dom Sibley prods forward to block.
Outside off, fuller, driven but straight to the cover fielder.
Pushed to covers now.
Good, quick run. Flighted on middle, nudged to square leg for a quick single.
Flat, on off, Joe goes on the back foot and pushes this to point. Comes ahead but then goes back and denies the single.
Prods forward to a full ball. Defended.
On middle, spinning down the leg side as DS leaves.
Tossed up on off, Dom comes ahead, looking to block but misses and gets hit on the pad. A stifled appeal but they know that the impact was outside off.
On middle, turning away from Dom, to the leg side, left alone.
Tossed up and on middle, Joe Root gets on his knees, Sweeps it behind square on the leg side. One run.
On middle, clipped to the on side. Rotates the strike, does Sibley.
IN THE AIR...SAFE! Flighted on middle, Root comes down the track and flicks this one to the right of Gill, at short leg, to deep square leg, for a single.
Outside off, short, Joe pushes this one to point for one.
Around off, loopy, Dom skips down and pushes this one to mid on for a quick single.
Outside off, fuller, left alone now.
On middle, fuller, kept out solidly by Dom.
Driven through covers for a single now by the English skipper.
Flighted, around off, turns away sharply as Root looked to play at this, but seeing the turn, gets his bat closer to the body and lets it through to Pant.
Short, on the pads, clipped to square leg for one.
Worked to the leg side for one.
Around off, flighted, Sibley's attempt to block only generates an outside edge, which goes to Rahane, at first slip, on the bounce.
The batsman has just blocked that from his crease.

NOT OUT! Ashwin was very confident but the wickets were missing this time around, due to the extra bounce. Flighted around middle this time, not much turn, as Sibley prods ahead, looking to block this one out. Misses and gets rapped on the pad. An appeal. A very, very, VERYYYYY excited appeal. But nothing from the umpire. Discussions going around and Ashwin wants the review. Kohli goes for it. Ultra Edge shows no bat. Ball Tracker shows that the on-field call was the right one as the ball seems to be missing the sticks.

Kohli has backed Ashwin and taken the review at the eleventh hour! Sibley is the man in question. Ashwin thinks he has trapped him LBW but the umpire does not. After a proper discussion, Kohli signals the 'T'.

IN THE AIR...SAFE! Pujara gets his fingertips to this one. Flighted, on leg, Sibley skips down and flicks this one uppish, to the left of Pujara, at leg slip, who gets his fingertips but is not able to hold on. Two runs.

Floated nicely, around off, turns away and misses Joe's forward defensive push. Pant collects and whips the bails, but Root was in the crease. A brilliant start for India and another good over by Patel!
That is defended solidly off the front foot.
Around off again, shorter in length, Root goes on the back foot and looks to block. The ball takes the inner half of the blade and goes to the leg side.
Around off, fuller, loopy, Dom skips down the track and clips this one through mid-wicket for one.
On middle, nudged to the right of the short leg fielder.
Flighted around off, pushed to the mid on region by Dom.
Dot to finish the over. England 2/5 after 2. They trail by 28 runs. Darted on middle and leg, Root manages to block it.
Sibley gets off the pair and gets his first run of this Test! Floated on middle, Sibley flicks it through square leg and gets a single.
Flighted on off, Sibley flicks it to short mid-wicket.
Shorter on off, Sibley defends it with a straight bat.
Darted around the pad, Root flicks it uppishly but away from short leg for one.
Floated around off, Root drives it through covers and looks for two. The throw is at the bowler's end. Ashwin whips the bails off but Sibley is back in.
Eventful first! Floated ball on off, Sibley blocks it and gets through the first over. A run and a two wickets off the first. Perfect for India.
The skipper gets the tourists scoreboard going. Short around off and turning away. Root dabs it to backward point and gets a single.
Shorter on off, Root gets on his back foot to defend but gets beaten due to the turn.
Will it be Axar's partner in crime, Ravichandran Ashwin from the other end? Yes, it is Ashwin!
Double blow for the English Lions! The skipper, Joe Root trudges out into the middle now.

OUT! BOWLED! Bairstow does not last long. Axar does not get the hat-trick but gets a wicket off the third ball of the innings. What a peach of a delivery this is from Axar, the local boy. Once again horrible technique from Bairstow. Floated delivery pitching on middle. Bairstow gets on the front foot and looks to defend expecting it to turn. The ball does not. Jonny leaves a 'not-so-bravo' gap between the bat and pad. The ball goes right between those and hits the top of leg.

NOT OUT! The review saves Bairstow! Terrible shot first up from Bairstow. He is on a pair and going for the sweep first up is a terrible choice. Bairstow has been given a lifeline here. Shorter delivery in middle, Bairstow looks to go for the premeditated sweep. He misses and gets hit on the mid-riff region. An appeal follows and the umpire raises his finger. Bairstow takes the review. Ultra Edge shows no bat. Time for the Ball Tracker and it shows the ball to be missing the stumps.
England review! Jonny Bairstow has been adjudged out for lbw right on his first ball! Ultra Edge shows that there is no bat on this one. The wickets are....MISSING! Scare for Jonny, but he survives!
Early blow for England! Jonny Bairstow comes out at Number 3!

OUT! BOWLED! Wicket off the very first delivery! Crawley who was magnificent in the first innings has gone for a golden duck. The local boy stuck in his very first ball of the first innings and he has done the same in the second innings. Terrible start for England! Perfect one for India.  Axar starts with a slowish delivery pitching on off. He gives this one air, the ball drifts and does not turn. Crawley looks to defend expecting it to spin but gets beaten by the straighter one and the ball hits the middle stump. What a stunning game this is turning out to be.

That is it from this game! The Pink Ball Test has not lasted long as India has decimated England and now they need to just avoid defeat in the next game to see themselves play in the final of the World Test Championship against New Zealand at Lord's. England is out of contention for that and has a lot of work to do if they are to level the Test series. The fourth and final Test of the series will begin on Thursday, 4th March 2021. That game will be a red ball Test and will begin at 0930 local (0400 GMT). Make sure you join us for that one. Till then, goodbye and take care!

The local lad, AXAR PATEL HAS BEEN NAMED AS THE PLAYER OF THE MATCH. He starts by saying that when things work out, it all looks easy and he just thinks about putting in the work and he just tries to keep things simple. Feels that he is happy that he is contributing with the ball for the team. On his strength, he says that he bowls wicket-to-wicket and makes things tough for the batters and he aims to not let the batters score a lot of runs. On being called Wasim Bhai by Pant, he says that Pant calls him that because they feel that his arm ball is very lethal, just like Wasim Akram's. States that he can bowl faster and also slower, but he smiles and says that what he is doing right now is working and so he will keep doing the same for now. Ends by saying that he will be happy if he can continue this form into the last Test.

The Indian captain, Virat Kohli, says that the result went their way but admits the quality of batting was not up to the standard by both teams. Tells they were looking to score more when they were at 100/3. Feels that the application from the batters was not right as he feels the pitch was better to bat on. Kohli says it was bizarre that 21 out of 30 wickets were off straight balls. Kohli feels the batters need to trust their defense a lot more and feels that is what Test cricket is all about. Kohli smiles and says Bumrah told that he is getting workload management while playing the Test and Ishant said that he is playing his 100th game, yet he is not bowling too much. Further adds that he told them to blame Axar as he is coming in and has just done the job. Kohli says he does not know what is the thing with Gujaratis and left-arm spinners as they always trouble the batters. Kohli says if the wicket offers something, Axar is very dangerous. On Ashwin, he says they need to stand up and take notice of what he has done. Adds he is happy that Ashwin plays for them. Kohli says they need to be ready for the hard grind, which they are. Adds a few extra days off with a tight schedule feels nice.

The losing skipper, Joe Root, starts off by saying that they were in a good position but they could not capitalize and it is something that they will look back on and try to learn and get better. Adds that they will come back stronger. Says that the plastic coating on the ball gathers pace off the wicket and if you put the ball on good areas, then you can make the ball talk. Further tells that they do not define themselves on this performance. Opines that they do not want to take the baggage across to the next game and they will look to build pressure for long periods. Further, he says that they have been able to pick wickets, as they have seen that in this game. On him being the bowler, he laughs and says that if he can scalp 5 wickets, you can tell that the wicket was doing a lot. Ends by congratulating Ishant for his 100th Test and also Ashwin for his 400 Test wickets.

The man of the moment, Ravichandran Ashwin, who has reached the feat of snaring 400 Test wickets is here for a chat! He says that it feels amazing and it is pleasant that it is happening in a winning cause and praises Axar for his performance too. Laughs and says that he is not able to get a grip about how these last 2-3 months have gone by and it all feels too dreamy. Adds that his effort in the lockdown has paid off. Says that he had a chat along with Ravi Shastri and Virat Kohli before the Australian tour, he said that they felt that he was bowling well. On his fitness, he says that his body is aging and he tried to get in better physical shape. Also adds that it is extra special to come back like this, after losing the first Test. On being asked if he is bowling his best, he laughs and says that that has been said about him before as well, in the 2015-16 season, where he went through his best phase but opines that whenever someone says he is at his best, he finds another gear and becomes even better and so he hopes that he can do the same now and continue becoming better.

So just a quick summary of the Test. England won the toss which was talk of the tinsel town and decided to bat. That decision did not do much as they were bowled out for 112 with Axar picking up a 5-fer. It looked like they had no chance but they managed to bowl out India for 145 and had a sniff but that did not last long as they had never got going in their second innings and were embarrassingly bowled out for 81. India chased down the score of 49 without breaking a sweat.

No matter how tough the wicket would be to bat on, defending 49 against India was always going to be next to impossible. The tourists tried their best were never in with a chance and a day that started with hope and dreams has ended in what one would call a proper beating and nightmare.

India was absolutely ballistic with the ball in the second session. The spin duo of Ashwin and Axar bowled 30 overs in tandem. The pair shared 9 wickets between them with Axar grabbing 5-fer and finishing the Test with 11-wickets and becoming the first bowler to pick 11 wickets in a Pink Ball Test. Ashwin's 4-fer in the second innings saw him become the 2nd fastest player to get 400 wickets in Test cricket. England never got going with the bat and were bowled out for their lowest total against India in Tests.

England started the day with a bang! They managed to restrict India to under 150 and restrict the lead to just 33, with skipper Joe Root finishing with 5/8 while Leach scalped 4/54. It looked like England had a chance to do something but that was just a false one. A memorable day at the brand new stadium here in Ahmedabad for India. They have outplayed, outclassed, and decimated the tourists.

What a day of Test match cricket! If anyone would have told that this game would end in two days, we are pretty sure everyone would have been laughing at that person but that is what has happened! The hype of the Pink Ball Test was longer than the actual Test as England threw away this Test and are out of contention to play the inaugural World Test Championship final against New Zealand at the Lord's! Emphatic win for India and from 1-0 down, they lead the series 2-1!

SIX! THAT'S THAT! Rohit Sharma listens to the crowd and finishes the game off with a maximum! Root goes fuller, flighted, around middle and off, Sharma skips down the track and bangs this one over deep mid-wicket. INDIA WIN BY 10 WICKETS AND ALSO LEAD 2-1 IN THE SERIES!
Full, yorker length, on middle, Rohit digs this one out. The crowds want Rohit Sharma to finish things off with a biggie!
FOUR! This was slammed away by Rohit! Root drags his length back and bowls a short one outside off, Sharma hammers this one through the covers for a boundary. 6 more needed now!

MISFIELD AND FOUR! Crawley is the culprit this time. Full, flighted, around off, Sharma gets on his knees and slogs this one towards the deep mid-wicket region. Zak runs to his left, tumbles and lets the ball through. 10 runs needed now.
Full, tossed up, on middle, punched to the cover region.
Shortish and on middle, nudged to the leg side now.
Presses forward to this full ball. Defends it out solidly, does Shubman Gill!
Around off, flatter, pushed to point again.
Short, around off, keeps slightly low too and pushes it to point.
On off, blocked.
Loopy on middle, whipped through square leg for one. Gill retains the strike for the next over. 14 more needed for the Indians.
Full, yorker length, on middle and leg, dug out by Rohit to the on side for a single.
Comes down the track and clips this one through mid on for a single by Gill.

NOT OUT! The review was more in hope, than anything else from Root. Full, flighted, on middle and leg, Gill comes down the track and looks to pad this one away and does so. The players appeal but the umpire does not think so. Root goes for the review as he tries his luck. No shot offered and hence, no Ultra Edge is needed. Ball Tracker shows that the wickets would be missing. Not out, it will be.
England have taken a review against Gill for LBW!
Flat again, outside off, slapped away but straight o Archer at point.
Short, on off, kept out.
Full, loopy, on middle and leg, Sharma prods ahead and looks to block but seems to have missed it. Gets hit on the pad and the English players register a tame appeal but nothing from the umpire.
Flat, on off, pushed away to point.
Well fielded by Jimmy this time. Shortish and outside off, Rohit goes back and slaps this one through point. Anderson does well to shuffle to his right and stop the ball.
FOUR! This time Rohit goes for the boundary. Uses his feet well too. Loopy and around off, Sharma dances down and powers this through mid on for a boundary.
Flighted on middle, Rohit presses forward and defends it out.
Short, around off, punched to covers.

SIX! Plays this shot so well. Gill wants to hurry back, by the looks of things. Full, tossed up, around off, Gill puts on his dancing shoes and skips down the track. Slams this one over long on for a biggie. 21 more needed.

FOUR BYES. Just not England's game. Nothing going their way now. You can't blame Foakes for this one. Flighted, but down the leg side, spinning away as well and Foakes is not able to grab this one. The ball races away to the fine leg fence.
Leg bye. Tossed up again, on leg too, Rohit looks to tuck it away but misses and the ball takes the pad and goes to the right of short fine leg. The batters take a leg bye.
Tossed up and on leg, Rohit pads this one away to the leg side.
Shortish on middle again, Rohit goes back and fends this one to the on side.
Short and on middle, kept out by Rohit.
Root to continue from the other end.
Darted on the middle pole, kept out by Shubman. 6 runs off this over. India need just 32 more runs now!
Short, wide, slashed away to the point fielder.
EDGY! Flighted around off, turns away as Gill looks to block it out. Takes the outside edge, goes past Ben at first slip, towards third man for a brace.
Gives it nice flight, outside off, spinning away and Gill makes a calculated leave.
Floated around off, pushed to the fielder at covers.
FOUR! A great stroke to get the last session underway. First boundary in this inning for young Gill. Flat, around off, Gill swivels and pulls this one nicely through mid-wicket.

We are back for the third session on Day 2, which also looks like it will be the final session of the Test. The Indian batters, Rohit Sharma and Shubman Gill make their way out into the middle. 38 more needed for them to take a well deserved lead of 2-1 in this series. Jack Leach to bowl for the visitors.
... DAY 2, FINAL SESSION ...

Excellent session for India! They managed to bowl out England first and then have also survived the two overs without losing any wicket. They are well on course to win this game. They need just 38 more runs to take an unassailable 2-1 lead in this 4-match Test series. England have been terrible in this session. Getting bowled out for 81 after doing so well in the first session will hurt the hosts a lot. This looks like a lost cause now but the tourists need to show some fight and make these 38 runs as difficult as possible.  Can the tourists do some miracle or will India cruise to victory? Join us for the final session of the day which might as well be the final one of the game.
Shorter on the pads, Sharma defends it to see off the session. DINNER ON DAY 2!
FOUR BYES! Flighted down the leg side, Rohit looks to flick but misses. Foakes misses it as well and the ball goes to the fence.
Short around off, Rohit taps it to point.
Gill is off the mark! Short on off and middle. Gill tucks it to mid-wicket for a run.
Flighted on leg, Gill comes down the track and pads it away.
Root starts with a short around off and middle. Rohit tucks it behind square leg for a single.

Excellent from Archer! A rare full toss on middle, Rohit whips it through mid-wicket. Archer gives it a chase and it looks like the ball will easily beat him to the fence. Archer though sprints and then puts the dive to save a run for his side.
Will we see Joe Root from the other end? Yes, we will!
Short on the pads, Rohit gets on his back foot and looks to defend but misses and gets hit on the pad.
Misfield and India will get off the mark! Floated on off, Rohit drives it to point. Anderson lets the ball go through him and he gets a couple to get off the mark.
Tossed up on off and turning away. Rohit looks to get bat on ball for the first time in this innings and he misses it.
Tossed up delivery around off, Sharma once again it happy to let that go.
Floated delivery around off, it spins away from Rohit. Sharma leaves it.
